brief:
Execute the approved consensus plan at .gjc/_session-019f1c30-3754-7000-b634-75d54f2dc70c/plans/ralplan/019f1c30-3754-7000-b634-75d54f2dc70c/pending-approval.md. Build crates/gjc-app-server: a codex-compatible JSON-RPC 2.0 app-server in Rust, embedded in-process via a crates/pi-natives app_server N-API wrapper, driving the TS AgentSession through an AgentBackend trait, hard-replacing gjc RPC mode + the notifications SDK after all dependents are migrated and green. Constraints: follow phase order strictly (Phase 0A blocking gates must be green before Phase 1); full concurrent running turns are a hard requirement (no single-active-turn cap); codex-core methods are lenient on unknown fields, gjc/* extensions are strict; non-goals = no fs/*/process/*, no real approval gate, no standalone binary. Every story must pass its named acceptance suites before checkpoint. Legacy deletion is atomic and last, gated by reference-search + all named suites.

@goal: Phase 0A blocking design gates
Scaffold crates/gjc-app-server (rlib) and crates/pi-natives app_server.rs skeleton. Deliver: multi-thread AgentSession singleton isolation audit + binding contract (per-thread scoped / read-only shared / non-blocking-safe serialized; unresolved singletons are escalated blockers, never a concurrency cap); per-thread scheduler design (serial mutating lane, cancel fast lane, read fast lane) with cross-thread concurrency; identity model (Rust-owned immutable threadId, mutable TS sessionId/sessionFile metadata, monotonic backendGeneration, stale-event rejection); Rust-derived TS + JSON Schema generation wired into root generate-schemas/check:schemas; pinned codex v1 method/field matrix encoded as tests; lenient codex-core + strict gjc/* unknown-field validators; item-lifecycle state machine skeleton with fixtures. Acceptance: app-server-conformance Phase 0 fixtures (schema validation, initialize errors, unsupported codex-core fields ignored, gjc unknown fields rejected, overload pre-admission -32001, stale-event rejection, TWO SIMULTANEOUS RUNNING TURNS, dispose-one-while-other-continues, item state-machine fixtures) green; check:schemas green; build:native compiles the N-API skeleton. No dependent migration starts until green.

@goal: Phase 1 core runtime and TS AgentBackend
Implement the AgentBackend trait + factory (create/resume/fork), ThreadRegistry, TS modes/app-server/app-server-mode.ts + agent-backend.ts, CLI `gjc app-server` (+ `--mode app-server` alias), and codex-core methods: initialize, initialized, thread/start, thread/resume, thread/fork (minimal), thread/read, thread/loaded/list, turn/start, turn/steer, turn/interrupt, subscription opt-out; core event state machine for userMessage/agentMessage/reasoning/terminal turns. Acceptance: app-server-conformance core lifecycle suite green; codex interop smoke minimal over stdio (extra codex-core fields ignored); check:schemas + build:native green; two concurrent running turns complete independently.

@goal: Phase 2 gjc extensions, command/exec, workflow gates, host tools/URIs
Implement namespaced gjc management methods mirroring the old RPC catalog (model set/cycle/list, compact + auto-compaction, state/read, thinking, steering/follow-up/interrupt modes, handoff, login/providers, set_todos, get_messages), unattended negotiation, workflow gate list/respond with validation + audit, host tool + host URI registration and request/update/result/cancel frames, command/exec + thread/shellCommand with commandExecution item streaming (base64/multiplexing), approvals no-op, compaction/retry/todo/notice/thinking/goal gjc events. Acceptance: app-server-conformance extension suite green incl. strict gjc/* unknown-field rejection; command/exec suite green with codex-core unknowns ignored; host tool/URI round-trip green; workflow gate suite green; check:schemas + build:native green.

@goal: Phase 3 transports and discovery
Implement production stdio (protocol-pure stdout), loopback WebSocket with private discovery file under .gjc/state/app-server + token handshake + stale cleanup + health checks, Unix socket with websocket upgrade + disconnect/reconnect, transport-level backpressure, reconnect resync (thread/read, thread/loaded/list, gjc/messages/get), token redaction. Acceptance: app-server-conformance transport suite green over stdio/WS/UDS; notifications-discovery suite green (WS discovery + token); codex interop smoke green over stdio and one local socket; check:schemas + build:native green.

@goal: Phase 4 harness migration
Rewrite packages/coding-agent/src/harness-control-plane/rpc-adapter.ts (GajaeCodeRpc) to spawn the app-server and speak JSON-RPC while preserving the HarnessRpc interface; single-flight acceptance = turn/start response + turn/started (or gjc/agent/start) after cursor with idle + empty-queue pre-state from gjc/state/read. Acceptance: harness adapter unit suite green; harness M10 e2e green against app-server; app-server-conformance regression (incl. two simultaneous running turns) green; check:schemas green. Old RPC remains for rollback until Phase 9.

@goal: Phase 5 Python gjc-rpc migration
Replace the legacy python/gjc-rpc client with an app-server JSON-RPC client + generated protocol types; parse codex turn/item notifications and gjc detail notifications; preserve high-level Python API names where useful (not legacy wire compat). Acceptance: python gjc-rpc tests green; app-server-conformance regression green; check:schemas green; add tests for initialize-with-ignored-codex-extras, thread/start, turn/start, command/exec, state read, workflow gates, host tools, reconnect, unknown-notification fallback, strict gjc unknown-field rejection.

@goal: Phase 6 robogjc migration
Update python/robogjc to spawn the app-server, initialize, start/resume threads from session_dir metadata, register GitHub host tools via gjc/hostTools/set, drive tasks with turn/start + turn/steer, preserving the sync worker.run_task model, credential redaction, audit writes, and per-issue serialization. Acceptance: robogjc tests green; bun run test:py green (gjc-rpc + robogjc); robogjc integration smoke green when env available; host tool audit tests (validation failure + happy path); check:schemas green. Old RPC remains for rollback.

@goal: Phase 7 notifications daemon migration
Move the Telegram/Discord/Slack clients to app-server WS discovery + gjc/notifications parity; implement action lifecycle semantics, inbound user_message + config commands, reconnect replay, lifecycle control. Acceptance: notifications e2e green for Telegram/Discord/Slack (WS discovery file + token, idle/action_needed/context_update/turn_stream/activity, inbound user_message, config command, pending-ask replay, first-valid-reply-wins, idempotent terminal resolution, duplicate-reply rejection, reconnect, stale cleanup); app-server-conformance notification suite + check:schemas green.

@goal: Phase 8 codex interop hardening
Run the pinned codex interop smoke and expand negative/compat tests: pre-init, duplicate init, unknown methods, malformed params, expectedTurnId mismatch, unsupported codex-core fields ignored, gjc/* unknown fields rejected, overload, opt-out, no approvals request, abort races, simultaneous running turns, command/exec streaming; validate sample frames against schema. Acceptance: codex interop smoke green; app-server-conformance full suite green; check:schemas + build:native green; architect re-checks method matrix, unknown-field policy, concurrency contract, and state-machine fixtures before deletion.

@goal: Phase 9 atomic legacy deletion
Only after Phases 4-8 are green: delete old RPC mode (CLI rpc/rpc-ui modes, runRpcMode dispatch, packages/coding-agent/src/modes/rpc, RpcClient exports + SDK types), legacy python protocol code, robogjc --mode rpc references, notifications SDK, native NotificationServer/NotificationControlServer exports, crates/gjc-notifications unfactored modules, obsolete docs/tests. Apply a reference-search dangling-ref gate after each deletion chunk (runRpcMode, RpcCommand, RpcResponse, rpc-client, --mode rpc, rpc-ui, NotificationServer, NotificationControlServer, gjc-notifications, notifications-sdk, docs/rpc, python gjc_rpc legacy frame names). Acceptance: reference-search gate clean or explicit keep rationale; harness M10 e2e, python gjc-rpc tests, robogjc tests, notifications e2e, codex interop smoke, app-server-conformance, check:schemas all green; final bun run check, bun run test, bun run build:native, bun run test:py all green.
